#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Dutiyacatumahārājasutta"
msgstr "38. The Four Great Kings (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ "
"velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the "
"Thirty-Three, recited this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ,"
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī;"
msgstr "would observe the sabbath"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca,"
msgstr "complete in all eight factors,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ;"
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya,"
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:2.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti."
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sā kho panesā, bhikkhave, sakkena devānamindena gāthā duggītā na sugītā "
"dubbhāsitā na subhāsitā."
msgstr ""
"But that verse was poorly sung by Sakka, lord of gods, not well sung; poorly "
"spoken, not well spoken."

msgctxt "an3.38:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.38:3.3"
msgid ""
"Sakko hi, bhikkhave, devānamindo aparimutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi "
"paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, aparimutto dukkhasmāti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Because Sakka, lord of gods, is not exempt from rebirth, old age, and death, "
"from sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. He is not exempt from "
"suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yo ca kho so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, "
"tassa kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kallaṃ vacanāya:"
msgstr ""
"But for a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, "
"and is rightly freed through enlightenment—it is appropriate to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ,"
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī;"
msgstr "would observe the sabbath,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca,"
msgstr "complete in all eight factors,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ;"
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya,"
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.38:5.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti."
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.145"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.38:6.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.38:6.2"
msgid ""
"So hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parimutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi "
"dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, parimutto dukkhasmāti vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Because that mendicant is exempt from rebirth, old age, and death, from "
"sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress. He is exempt from "
"suffering, I say.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.38:6.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
